    <string name="welcome">Welcome!</string>
    <string name="instructions_title">Version %s</string>
    <string name="instructions_method_title">Concept</string>
    <string name="instructions_method_text">
        This app allows you to learn the words even if you think that you are just too lazy to do it. \n\n
        Once you have added new words to your dictionary, they start appearing as notifications,
        making it impossible for you to miss them.
        \n\n
        The click on a notification shows the word you would want to translate and some possible translations from which
        you have to pick a correct one. The key idea is that the notifications can only be closed by picking the correct translation of the word.
        \n\n
        This whole system makes you repeat the words you learn every day (at most), which ensures remembering the word,
        while putting nearly no effort in learning.\n
        Basically, the app takes away all your responsibility to learn 5 or 10 new words every day.
    </string>
    <string name="instructions_guess_trans_title">Guessing Translation</string>
    <string name="instructions_guess_trans_text">
        The app partially relies on the offline dictionaries support. They are used only as a helper.
        \n\n
        That is - when you want to enter a new word via \"Add New Words\" screen, once you click on the "Translation"
        field you will get some possible translations, you may have wanted to use.
        \n\n
        This saves you time, you really don\'t want to spend on switching the keyboard layout from one language to the
        other.
    </string>

    <string name="instructions_dict_help_title">Information About Dictionaries</string>
    <string name="instructions_dict_help_text">
        To use a helping dictionary you have to download it and put into your phone\'s memory.
        I provide packages that do it for you at least for some languages. \n
        If your language is still missing - contact me and we will try to solve the problem.
        \n\n
        However, if you want to do it manually:
        The dictionaries should be put to the sd card, into the folder \"LearnIt\"
        (you may want to click \"Export dictionary\" inside the app - this will create the folder automatically)
        If you have any ideas, I would love to hear them.\n\n
        The dictionaries should be put in the folder {language_from}-{language_to}. \n\n
        StarDict usually is distributed with 3 files *.ifo, *.idx, *.dict. They all have to have name \"dict\".\n\n
        So for German-English dict the path looks as follows:\n\n
        /SD_CARD/LearnIt/de-en/dict.ifo\n
        /SD_CARD/LearnIt/de-en/dict.idx\n
        /SD_CARD/LearnIt/de-en/dict.dict\n
    </string>

    <string name="instructions_edit_words_help_title">Editing Existing Words</string>
    <string name="instructions_edit_words_help_text">
        While you are on \"My Dictionary\" screen, and you have some words from your dictionary showing in the list, you may
        long-click them and edit/delete them.
    </string>

    <string name="instructions_thank_you_title">Thank You!</string>
